What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it Credit/D and you'll have a far less stressful experience, as the workload was fairly intensive. Two midterms, 6 cases, and weekly homeworks that aren't collected. Interesting if you want to know more about/work with markets.

Must take for anyone who has previous finance background and is seriously interested in making a career in the financial industry. It is a HARD class but you work a lot and you learn from the struggle.
